==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Esthesiometer
<hw>Es*the`si*om"e*ter</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr></mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ (see
<er>⟦AE⟧sthesia</er>) + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument to
measure the degree of sensation, by determining at how short a distance
two impressions upon the skin can be distinguished, and thus to
determine whether the condition of tactile sensibility is normal or
altered.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>AEsthesis</ent>⟦br⟧
